 to evaluate such models to enhance their credibility in the forthcoming value in health paper empirically evaluating decision analytic model the models being developed by researchers throughout the country have helped us to assess the long term effectiveness and costs of various interventions for example how hpv vaccination and cervical screening might be used to prevent cervical cancer goldhaber fiebert said but we believe it is important to carefully review these modeling approaches and to compare them to independent studies are the models consistent with real world study findings an important question in light of the increasing use of models to inform comparative effectiveness considerations for policymaking goldhaber fiebert and co authors harvard faculty members natasha stout and sue goldie conducted a structured literature review of articles comparing model and study outcomes they found strong support for this approach but also a lack of consistency in how models are evaluated they developed recommendations for reporting model evaluations to reduce discrepancies and help in future comparisons of study and model outcomes we found a need for a more uniform approach to model evaluations goldhaber fiebert said comparisons of modeled outcomes to real world study results build credibility and promote transparency reporting such comparisons in a consistent way allows thorough evaluation necessary to understand how useful the models really are related links jeremy goldhaber fiebert assistant professor of medicine empirically evaluating decision analytic models jeremy goldhaber fiebert stout nk goldie sj value health 2010 search chp search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest health reform forum brings together stanford's experts to assess implications of new health law april 2 2010 news stanford health policy researchers receive nia challenge grant to study hiv treatment november 11 2009 news stanford health policy welcomes global health corps fellows for orientation august 12 2009 chp pcor fsi stanford announcement stanford health policy associate lists five steps to boost impact of comparative effectiveness research june 16 2009 news lecture on health care policy at stanford september 16 2008 news emerging pet technology is more accurate than widely used ct scan in staging lung cancer stanford va study shows november 25 2003 press release support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 736 0815 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
